      • formatMSL

        public static java.lang.String formatMSL​(GeoPoint point)
        Format the altitude in ft MSL for display.
        Parameters:
        point - GeoPoint instance with the HAE altitude value specified
        Returns:
        A String containing altitude in MSL in the format of "NN.NN ft MSL" where N is a number or if the altitude is unknown, return -- ft MSL.

      • formatMSL

        public static java.lang.String formatMSL​(GeoPoint point,
                                         double surfaceHAE)
        Format the altitude in ft MSL for display given a geopoint in AGL.
        Parameters:
        point - GeoPoint instance with the AGL altitude value specified
        surfaceHAE - the HAE value of the current location and is used only if the point is AGL otherwise will be ignored.
        Returns:
        A String containing altitude in MSL in the format of "NN.NN ft MSL" where N is a number or if the altitude is unknown, return -- ft MSL.

      • formatMSL

        public static java.lang.String formatMSL​(GeoPoint point,
                                         Span span)
        Format the altitude in the specified units for the specified reference for display.

        Currently the only references supported are AltitudeReference#MSL and GeoPoint.AltitudeReference.HAE. Use of other references will cause an IllegalArgumentException to be thrown.

        Parameters:
        point - The point containing the altitude to be formatted
        span - The conversion of the MSL units (feet/meters/yards)
        Returns:
        A formatted string with the altitude units in the specified units based on the specified reference with the altitude reference abbreviation as a suffix.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If formatRef is not one of the references supported by this method.
